<p>I'm creating a program in C# that download the string from an HTML page, get only the informations I want and shows it in two different listboxes! (This is already done and working) The thing is those two listboxes contains two different informations found on the same webpage, and I want to have them on the same line to save it into a txt file.</p>  <p>Example: "StarWars" and "1977"</p>  <p>The idea I had was to add <code>listboxitem1</code> next to <code>secondlistboxitem1</code> in a richtextbox. But I can't find a solution</p>  <p><a href="http://puu.sh/kfspZ/83f3dbb9d6.png" rel="nofollow">http://puu.sh/kfspZ/83f3dbb9d6.png</a></p>  <p>(I don't know how to put code in a post so here is a picture of my code)</p>  <p>I know I'm certainly doing this in the wrong way because I'm a beginner.</p>  <p>Cordially (edit to add code)</p>  <pre><code> private void button1_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)     {         List&lt;string&gt; prices = new List&lt;string&gt;();         List&lt;string&gt; servers = new List&lt;string&gt;();         string url = "http://www.gametradeeasy.com/game-dofus-kamas-id_10007.html";         WebClient web = new WebClient();         string result = web.DownloadString(url);         richTextBox1.Text = result;         string bug = "\"";         MatchCollection m1 = Regex.Matches(result, @"&lt;font color=" + bug + "#990000" + bug + @"&gt;\s*(.+?)\s*&lt;/font&gt;", RegexOptions.Singleline);         MatchCollection m2 = Regex.Matches(result, @"width=" + bug + "13%" + bug + " title=" + bug + @"\s*(.+?)\s*-Kamas", RegexOptions.Singleline);         foreach(Match m in m1)         {             string price = m.Groups[1].Value;             prices.Add(price);            // richTextBox2.Text += (price + "\n");         }         foreach(Match m in m2)         {             string server = m.Groups[1].Value;             servers.Add(server);          }         listBox1.DataSource = servers;         listBox2.DataSource = prices;     } </code></pre>